## PHASE D — Distribution polish (remainder)

### D5. Distribution polish
- [x] macOS Keychain for the CredentialStore — DONE 2026-06-21. Keychain is now
      the DEFAULT at-rest backend (was opt-in): isKeychainEnabled defaults on,
      opt out with SYNCRONA_USE_KEYCHAIN=0, graceful fallback to machine key when
      @napi-rs/keyring/keychain is unavailable; decrypt retries with the machine
      key so pre-D5 stores keep opening. + clearStoreKeyCache, hermetic test
      harness (jest.setup.js forces keychain off; storeKey/storeKeyResolution
      mock the keyring). Docs synced (core README, packaging README, install.ps1).
- [x] Homebrew formula — DONE (code-complete, UNVERIFIED) 2026-06-21:
      packaging/homebrew/syncro-now-ai.rb (Node-CLI pattern). Cannot brew-install
      until first npm publish + tap repo exist.
- [x] GitHub Actions to auto-update the Homebrew formula on each release — DONE
      2026-06-21: dormant `update-homebrew` job in release.yml (computes sha256
      from the published tarball, renders the formula, pushes to the tap). Gated
      on HOMEBREW_TAP_READY var + HOMEBREW_TAP_TOKEN secret.
- [x] Windows: PowerShell install script + Windows Credential Manager — DONE
      2026-06-21: packaging/windows/install.ps1 (Node check + global npm install);
      Windows Credential Manager comes from the cross-platform @napi-rs/keyring
      used by D5. UNVERIFIED (no Windows host).

**Definition of Done for Phase D:** `brew install syncrona && syncrona login && syncrona init` works
(blocked only on the first npm publish + tap repo — both owner-gated).

