## Remaining from the ARCHITECTURE REVIEW (2026-06-11) — details in DONE
- [x] AR1 (residual): RESOLVED 2026-06-12 evening — the .env values were test
      fixtures (Tyler/Edwards/dev90755) written by cred.test.ts, whose broken
      top-level cleanup resurrected the file after every test run. Test fixed
      (commit 06d307c): awaited writes + afterAll cleanup; .env no longer
      lingers on disk. No evidence of a real password — rotate only if real
      credentials were ever placed there manually. See also CR2.
- [x] AR2 (residual): DONE 2026-06-21 — at-rest key resolves SYNCRONA_STORE_KEY > OS keychain (opt-in SYNCRONA_USE_KEYCHAIN, @napi-rs/keyring) > legacy machine key, with decrypt fallback. See DONE.
- [ ] AR9 (residual): Full ts-jest migration of the mcp-server tests — DEFERRED
      2026-06-21, RE-CONFIRMED 2026-06-24 (conscious decision, not a gap): HIGH
      RISK for ZERO behavior change. Concretely it means rewriting 12 test files
      / ~4800 lines from the node:test + assert/strict API (run against dist via
      `npm run build && node --test`) to ts-jest/expect against src, AND replacing
      the custom coverage gate (scripts/check-coverage-gate.js parses node --test
      coverage) plus the governance node:test harness. Testing the compiled dist
      is a legitimate choice (it exercises the shipped artifact); the dispatch
      logic already has dedicated tests. New tests are written in the existing
      node:test/dist style instead.
- [x] AR11: DONE 2026-06-21 — TOOL_METRICS (the in-memory ring buffer) is no
      longer an exported, externally-spliced array. It is encapsulated behind
      getToolMetrics / clearToolMetrics / replaceToolMetrics / pushToolMetric in
      toolService.ts (mirrors clearServiceNowSecretsCache / clearScopedApiPrefixCache),
      so it is mutated in one place and reset/rehydrated explicitly. index.ts and
      toolModules.ts use the accessors; 5 tests (toolMetrics.test.js).

