      packages, which also got their first unit tests. Baseline scores:
      sn-transport 80.2%, credential-store 47.0% total (covered 70%; the
      uncovered remainder is the keychain/native path). Stryker added as a devDep
      (does not affect the prod `npm audit --omit=dev` gate).
- [x] **G14. Performance baseline** — DONE 2026-06-21: `npm run bench`
      (scripts/bench.mjs) processes a deterministic synthetic manifest (default
      40 tables × 80 records = 3200 records / 4280 files) through the pure
      summarize → Mermaid → doc-body pipeline; prints median/p95/mean + runs/sec
      after warm-up. Tunable (--tables/--records/--iterations) and gateable
      (--max-ms exits non-zero) so it can run as a non-blocking CI job. No new
      deps; imports the compiled core. (Kept out of the blocking `check` chain on
      purpose — wall-clock thresholds are flaky across CI runners.)
- [x] **G15. OS matrix in CI** — DONE 2026-06-13: live CI is now
      .github/workflows/ci.yml (the repo lives on GitHub; azure-pipelines.yml
      does not run there), matrix ubuntu-latest + macos-latest, Node from
      .nvmrc, full check chain. Windows remains with D5/DX1.
- [x] **G16. Security automation in CI** — DONE 2026-06-16: `npm audit
      --omit=dev --audit-level=high` runs in the GitHub Actions workflow
      (0 vulnerabilities). Added: gitleaks secret scanning (full-history job in
      ci.yml, test/example fixtures allowlisted via .gitleaks.toml; free on this
      personal private repo), CodeQL SAST (.github/workflows/codeql.yml — push/PR;
      analyze job guarded to `github.event.repository.private == false` so it
      stays inert until the repo is public, then activates automatically), and
      Dependabot (.github/dependabot.yml — weekly npm + github-actions updates).
      All actions SHA-pinned, least-privilege permissions.
- [x] **G17. Tests must not dirty the tracked tree** — DONE 2026-06-13: the
      culprit was commandsDownload.test.ts — downloadCommand calls the REAL
      generateScopeDocs(man), which resolves its outDir from process.cwd() and
      so rewrote packages/core/docs/scopes/x_test.md (cwd = packages/core under
      jest) with a fresh timestamp every run. Fixed by stubbing ../scopeDocs in
      that test (the test is about download orchestration, not doc generation).
      Verified: full core suite leaves the tracked tree clean.

